Dec 12 2008 	Great location but very noisy	The location was excellent, the best I've ever experienced for such a low price. Staff were very nice. However, my three nights at Pickwick Hall were somewhat nightmareish... It has to be said that I was in London to take a course and had to get up really early. Getting a good night's sleep was essential - and I certainly did not succeed at this hostel!!! Street noise was terrible, even with heavy-duty earplugs. The room was cold and the mattress uncomfortable. I wasn't mad about the showers and one of the toilets didn't flush properly... I would only return to Pickwick Hall if I knew I was spending most of the night out partying.	
Jul 15 2008 	Mediocre	Stayed there for a couple of months when studying in London...it's cheap and centrally located, but that's about it. The mattresses are terrible and will kill your back. There's usually about 20 random college kids just lurking around the kitchen. They advertise free breakfast, but it's just toast and jelly. There is an illusion of security, but that didn't stop my laptop from being stolen. Apparently Pickwick (unlike hostels in uber safe places like Greece and Italy) doesn't require a passport from transient guests, so your roommate/new best friend named Tom can really be some Hungarian hanging around waiting to steal your stuff, and once he's gone, there's no way to find out his real identity.	
Jun 25 2008 	Great Place to get over jet lag	Pickwick Hall was our first stop on our big Euro trip. We arrived after being awake for 30hours and found it a fantastic place to chill out and catch up on some much needed rest. Definitely not a party place, the plumbing is terrible , bathrooms need a bit more of a clean and place is very dated BUT the linen is clean, the bed is comfy, a short walk to the Tube and Sainsbury's and the common areas were a great place to meet and chat with other travellers. We'd recommend it for somewhere quiet to rest up for a few days.	
Apr 29 2008 	Loved it!	My boyfriend and I took our first European trip together and stayed in Pickwick Hall in London for a week. I had studied previously in the Bloomsbury area and wanted to book something in that vicinity since I knew where the Tube stops, grocery stores, etc. were. We had a very nice room with a double bed and our own bathroom, so that was fantastic! We also had a fridge and microwave in our room so we did some grocery shopping and made it our little home for the week. The staff, especially Patrick was charming, and he was downstairs every morning with the complimentary breakfast asking if we'd like some tea. I found the setting to be very nice, quiet, pleasant, and safe. We've already recommended it to some friends and would definitely stay there in the future.	
Sep 24 2007 	a great budget option for London	I stayed at Pickwick Hall three times in as many months and became rather attached to this charming hostel. The Bloomsbury location is fantastic - safe and quiet, and a very short walk to the British Museum. Patrick was a somewhat reserved but delightful and helpful host. The rooms were very spacious and clean, if a little shabby, and one of the bathrooms had a vague smell of mould but this was a small quibble. The free internet (two terminals) was a bonus, and there is a washing machine in the basement. Breakfast was basic but good, and the kitchen very clean, with the welcome inclusion of a dishwasher. Excellent value for money by London standards. I would definitely return to Pickwick Hall.	
