Jan 8 2007 	Good basic lodging!	Needing a place to crash for a few days in London on my way to Istanbul, I decided to give Pickwick Hall a try and overall, way satisfied with my choice.I received a friendly greeting for the owner, Patrick, upon my arrival and was quickly shown to a small but decent room.The room was clean (except for the carpet, which needed a good scrub and the walls could have used a lick of paint) as were the shared bathrooms.Granted, this is not the place for a romantic weekend, but idea for budget travellers.Being a theatre fan, the location was great, with the theatre district a mere 20 minute walk away.Restaurants and grocery stores were located nearby.The breakfast was good and the internet free - big pluses in pricey London.5 minute walk to Holborn Tube and Russell Square tube stations.I would definitely return.	
