Aug 9 2006 	Worth picking	I stayed at Pickwick at the end of July in 2006. It was an excellent price for a London hostel. Overall I found it to be clean (including he towel and sheet provided) and the staff person to be nice. It wasn't fancy, but that's not what you get from hostels, is it? There was free internet to be had and the breakfast was basic (eg cerial, toast, coffee etc.) . The location was great. Literally a 5 minute walk from the British musem. Not far from SoHo if you're looking to go out for the evening, you're in a good spot. My room had a mini-fridge, and a microwave. The only drawback I could see is that there wasn't any air con (no surprise) so I could see the place getting hot. Hope this helps.	
Nov 3 2005	More than a hostel	Spent four nights at the Pickwick Hall in Bloomsbury in October. It was our first hostel experience (we're a middle aged Canadian couple) and it was delightful. So quiet and welcoming. Patrick and Staff could not have been more helpful with directions and suggestions. The room in the basement was large and airy..came complete with desk, large closet, microwave and fridge and hair dryer..very clean and comfortable beds. The free internet in the TV lounge was a great surprise and we used it daily. Lots of travel info available in the lobby...also access to laundry &amp; telephones. The price was 49£ per night for a double ensuite and included a wee continental breakfast. Within walking distance to Sir John Sloane's &amp; British Museums. Holborn tube Stn. is a five minute walk and is where at least two London Walks originate. The area is very safe with several lovely green spaces nearby. We would stay again..Sharon &amp; CarlCanada	
